<br>
By themselves, the post 60 pets should only exceed the epic in their areas of expertise (earth HPs, air mitigation/stuns, etc.) ONLY if utilized well, and only by a bit.<br>
<br>
During the Epic 2 quest, you have to combine the 1st epic in a container (as was suggested earlier) with some decently difficult items to obtain (not INSANE difficult, but challenging difficult).  When you get the Epic 2, you discover *gasp* that instead of being a new pet, or even a new 1hb primary slot partical weapon, It is instead something ENTIRELY different.<br>
<br>
My proposed Epic 2:<br>
<br>
Magic Lore No Drop (and NOT summoned by a new spell)<br>
<br>
AMMO SLOT<br>
<br>
The item itself has no stat modifiers (since items placed in the ammo slot do not use their stats if they have any).  Instead, it gives the magician Ultravision, See Invis, a Rigth Click Effect (I dunno, how bout a pet only ATK increase that stacks with Burnout?  or a Self only 50 point DS? lets not get TOO crazy here) AND, it acts as a Focus for the post 60 pets (but not for the epic).<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
In this way, doing the 1st epic quest will be necessary to get to the 2nd epic.  The epic pet BY ITSELF will be stronger than the post 60 pets, but the 60 pets after being FOCUSED will be noticeably stronger than the epic, given their areas of expertise.  The fact that it wouldn't focus the Epic would keep people from being lazy about elemental summoning choices.  Oh, and I suppose the effects of the focus would HAVE to stack with the VT mage Gloves, so those who have the time investment to get the gloves still get the advantatage they earned.<br>
<br>
<br>
That's my idea for this problem, what ya think? <p>After working out the kinks of his new incantations, Knobby decides a Poo Elemental wasn't such a good idea after all...
